<h1>Case 12 — Rapid Response Network</h1>

<h2>Brief Description</h2>
<p>
The Rapid Response Network integrates all emergency services—including ambulance, fire units, 
police patrols, and disaster teams—into a unified intelligent system. 
It ensures the fastest possible response by assigning the right team and route for every emergency.
</p>

<h2>Rising Problems</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Delayed emergency response due to inefficient coordination.</li>
    <li>Difficulty in choosing the correct team for a specific type of emergency.</li>
    <li>Lack of backup units when the nearest teams are busy.</li>
    <li>Unoptimized routes causing delays and resource wastage.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Solutions / Logic Used</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Hash Tables:</strong> Maintain database of emergency units, status, and specializations.</li>
    <li><strong>Priority Queue:</strong> Rank emergency calls based on severity and urgency.</li>
    <li><strong>Queue:</strong> Handle incoming emergency calls and assign them sequentially.</li>
    <li><strong>Dijkstra’s Algorithm:</strong> Find the fastest route to reach the location.</li>
    <li><strong>BFS:</strong> Scan for nearest backup units when primary responders are unavailable.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Suitable SDGs</h2>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 3 — Good Health & Well-Being</strong>
    <p>Improves survival rates and emergency outcomes through rapid medical response.</p>
</div>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 11 — Sustainable Cities & Communities</strong>
    <p>Strengthens urban resilience and ensures quick disaster management.</p>
</div>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 9 — Industry, Innovation & Infrastructure</strong>
    <p>Implements intelligent emergency systems and modern routing technology.</p>
</div>

